12/11/2006
VATICAN CITY, Vatican -- Pope Benedict XVI will not be meeting with Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan during his upcoming visit to Turkey. According to the itinerary for the trip, released by the Vatican over the weekend, the visit will begin with a visit to the tomb of Kemal Ataturk, the founder of modern Turkey, and talks with Turkish dignitaries on November 28th. He is also expected to meet with Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew as part of efforts towards reconciliation between the Catholic and Orthodox churches.
Erdogan's office said in a statement that the prime minister would be in Latvia for a NATO summit during the first two days of the visit. After he returns, he will busy with other meetings, the statement said. (Reuters - 11/11/06, 10/11/06)
